      "description": "Google Gemma 4 (Apache-2.0) — multimodal open models with agentic skills, multi-step planning, and audio-visual processing. The e2b/e4b edge variants use per-layer activations: ~2 GB / ~3 GB resident at runtime despite a larger on-disk footprint, which keeps Pi 5, NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano, and 8 GB Macs comfortably inside their memory budget alongside the ASR worker. The 26B MoE and 31B dense tiers scale up for workstation-class hardware. Every tier pairs with Moonshine on Pi-class hardware and Parakeet TDT on capable hardware so the same machine can run text + audio together.",
